[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man remanded on Galashiels pensioner robbery charge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been remanded in custody after being accused of assaulting an 85-year-old woman to her severe injury and robbing her of her handbag.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It followed an incident in Croft Street, Galashiels, on 10 September.
Alexander Watson, 33, of Galashiels, made no plea or declaration during a private hearing at Jedburgh Sheriff Court.
The case was continued for further examination and he was remanded in custody by Sheriff Peter Paterson.
